[http://www.flickr.com/photos/27331537@N06]  That leaves two other options - Queen Victoria's Golden Jubilee (1887) - too early no trams in King Street then - or her Diamond Jubilee in 1897. The civic fathers (no civic 'mothers' in those days) would be more likely to erect a 'Victoria the Good' sign for her Diamond Jubilee than Federation. Therefore, suggest respectfully, that the caption should read

&quot;King Street, Sydney, decorated for Queen Victoria's Diamond Jubilee - 1897&quot;

John
